name: pipeline construction, natural gas, low pressure distribution network | pipeline, natural gas, low pressure distribution network | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8696/documentation

Pipeline infrastructure for gas distribution. Life time 40 years. Annual transport of about 110 PJ over 16'000 km including the house connecting pipelines; Geography: Data is based on Swiss data.;Material requirements of the pipeline system are round 3.3t/km steel, 6.1 t/km cast iron, 4.2t/km PE, 26.8 t/km gravel, 360t/km sandt. These values are calculated based on the material density, the thickness of the pipeline wall and the kilometers of the various pipeline types.



This dataset describes the infrastructure needed for the Swiss low (<0.1 bar) pressure distribution network.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/422:Construction of utility projects/4220:Construction of utility projects

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Data is based on Swiss data.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: The length of the pipelines is based on statistics, whereas the thickness of the pipeline is estimated.
